File: The army has been deployed in Cape Town's crime-riddled townships on Thursday afternoon. * Editor's note: You can read an updated version of this breaking news story here. CAPE TOWN - The army has been deployed in Cape Town's crime-riddled townships on Thursday afternoon. Police minister Bheki Cele on Sunday told the Philippi community the army will be visible in the area in the week. READ: Cape residents pin hope on army He told residents that the deployment would last three months. Neighbourhoods including Bonteheuwel, Delft, Hanover Park and Philippi East have been plagued by gang-related violence.